    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.classes.Item.q0sZTVGHE77Di2VU]{Solarian, Enhanced}</p>\n<p>When you have made significant progress attuning yourself to your stellar mode, you can sacrifice that greater attunement in exchange for momentary benefits.</p>\n<p>While you have 2 attunement points in a stellar mode, you can expend 2 attunement points on your turn without spending an action to gain two effects until the beginning of your next turn. First, you gain benefits from that modeâ€™s stellar revelations as though you were fully attuned, rather than attuned. Second, you gain a benefit based on which mode you are attuned to.</p>\n<p><strong>Energy:</strong> You temporarily gain the @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.feats.Item.seWKgVZbtyOPhl6e]{Nimble Moves} feat.</p>\n<p><strong>Graviton:</strong> Your insight bonus to Reflex saves applies to all your saving throws.</p>\n<p><strong>Photon:</strong> The first time you deal damage to a creature, you can increase your insight bonus to damage from photon mode to 1d4, plus 1d4 for every 6 solarian levels you have. If your attack or effect damages multiple creatures, you apply this additional damage to only one target of your choice; the rest take the default photon mode damage (+1 insight bonus damage). At 12th level, you can apply this higher damage to up to two targets of your choice.</p>\n<p><strong>Resistance:</strong> In addition to granting you DR, resistance mode also grants you resistance 1 to acid, cold, electricity, fire, and sonic damage. This increases by 1 for every 6 solarian levels you have. This energy resistance stacks with one other source of energy resistance you have (such as from equipment).</p>\n<p><em>Enable/Disable Resistance modifiers in the Modifier tab.</em></p>"
    },
